"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-finance-personalfinance-1931207-olympic-athletes-salary-paid\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  As the Olympic Games in Paris are in full swing, numerous athletes have already bagged substantial paydays by reaching the podium.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 26, \"end\": 31, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999618012, \"rank\": 3.8366171546701295e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the amount they receive depends more on the country they represent than the medal they win.\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee does not offer any prize money to participants or winners.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 239, \"end\": 270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, those who make it to the podium this year will receive their medal and a surprise gift box, reportedly containing an Olympics poster and a plushie of the mascot, the red triangular Phryge.\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 527, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The responsibility for prize pots and financial assistance before the games falls to the National Olympic Committees.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 618, \"end\": 645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999329321953718, \"rank\": 6.70723031006562e-05, \"text\": \"National Olympic Committees\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, World Athletics and the International Boxing Association have announced they will be distributing some prize money this year.\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999990518518, \"rank\": 9.48049087395856e-10, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 682, \"end\": 714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2786982343860903e-15, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The UK is among the few countries that do not provide a direct cash reward for podium placements.\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999974070306, \"rank\": 2.5928168991667305e-09, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, British Athletics has taken the initiative to offer medal bonuses separate from the government.\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 892, \"end\": 899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999930137164, \"rank\": 3.7559737724117884e-09, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB instead receives grants before their Olympic appearance to fund their training and increase their chances of podium finishes.\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 1122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE:Transgender boxer wants Imane Khelif banned from Olympics as gender row explodes  Asreported by CNBC, Hong Kong tops the list in rewarding its elite athletes, dishing out a whopping $768,000 (\\u00a3603,000) for Olympic gold medallists, while silver and bronze bring home $384,000 (\\u00a3301,000) and $192,000 (\\u00a3150,000) respectively.\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1134, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.0555951067851254e-12, \"text\": \"Transgender\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\"}, {\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 1230, \"end\": 1234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 0.9999999501042124, \"rank\": 4.989577246236544e-08, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1236, \"end\": 1245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.9999998636763032, \"rank\": 1.2734573048693294e-07, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Singapore offers similar lucrative rewards, and Indonesia is not far behind, providing $300,000 (\\u00a3235,000) for gold, with silver and bronze winners receiving lesser amounts.\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1458, \"end\": 1467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.586243598655778e-12, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999673159442, \"rank\": 3.126134845607594e-08, \"text\": \"Indonesia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In contrast, Germany's Sports Aid Foundation extends financial rewards beyond the top three, reaching out to those securing up to the 8th position.\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1646, \"end\": 1653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.9679385984686919, \"rank\": 0.031888604001179294, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the other end of the pay scale, Australia's rewards are modest at best, offering $13,000 (\\u00a310,000) for gold, with smaller sums for other medals.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1816, \"end\": 1825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999978414880947, \"rank\": 1.933280153553359e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it's not just about the money.\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes often benefit from additional perks for instance, gold medal winners from Kazakhstan receive $250,000 (\\u00a3196,000) as well as housing.\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2053, \"end\": 2063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"score\": 0.9999999949081939, \"rank\": 4.0517924785671685e-09, \"text\": \"Kazakhstan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Malaysian athletes too can strike gold beyond government provisions, with the Malaysian National Sports Council offering $215,000(\\u00a3168,000)-$22,000 (\\u00a317,000).\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2113, \"end\": 2131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Malaysian athletes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2191, \"end\": 2200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\", \"score\": 0.9959683057075834, \"rank\": 0.004041432917218565, \"text\": \"Malaysian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\"}, {\"begin\": 2201, \"end\": 2224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999630255152593, \"rank\": 3.6975830528157794e-05, \"text\": \"National Sports Council\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Local companies add to the pot with lavish apartments and cash bonuses, plus a \\\"foreign-made car\\\" has been promised by Youth and Sports Minister Hannah Yeoh according to local reports.\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2417, \"end\": 2428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Yeoh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hannah Yeoh\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Yeoh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Yeoh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss:Jake Paul's offer to boxer that quit against Khelif after failing gender test  Do not miss:Tennis star makes odd request to Olympics chiefs after losing quarter-final  Do not miss:Judy Murray shares biggest regret after Andy retires from tennis at Olympics  Even life-long culinary delights have been offered up, with one food chain promising Malaysian medalists free sustenance and teh tarik indefinitely.\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2470, \"end\": 2479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jake Paul\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\"}, {\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Judy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2813, \"end\": 2822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\", \"score\": 0.9959683057075834, \"rank\": 0.004041432917218565, \"text\": \"Malaysian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Korean Olympic medalists are rewarded with a pension on top of their prize money, while those from Hong Kong are gifted free lifetime tickets from the country's public transit operator.\", \"from\": 2878, \"to\": 3069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2884, \"end\": 2890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9515210089170186, \"rank\": 0.050948225501380756, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2983, \"end\": 2992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.9999998636763032, \"rank\": 1.2734573048693294e-07, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Polish athletes this year are also set to receive an array of private and government gifts including a painting, holiday voucher, scholarship and even a diamond for securing a podium position.\", \"from\": 3070, \"to\": 3262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3070, \"end\": 3076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland\", \"score\": 0.93226089608355, \"rank\": 0.0626428576721269, \"text\": \"Polish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the more unusual rewards in Olympic history include Japanese table tennis player Kasumi Ishikawa who was given 100 bags of rice after winning a silver medal at the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 3264, \"to\": 3448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3324, \"end\": 3332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9956376882166345, \"rank\": 0.003238812658146515, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3353, \"end\": 3368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kasumi_Ishikawa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kasumi Ishikawa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13382519\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kasumi_Ishikawa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kasumi_Ishikawa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indonesian badminton gold medalists Apriyani Rahayu and Greysia Polii were reportedly gifted five cows, a meatball restaurant and a new house.\", \"from\": 3449, \"to\": 3591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3449, \"end\": 3459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.9993602285219113, \"rank\": 0.0006399822683925254, \"text\": \"Indonesian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}, {\"begin\": 3485, \"end\": 3500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apriyani_Rahayu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Apriyani Rahayu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apriyani_Rahayu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apriyani_Rahayu\"}, {\"begin\": 3505, \"end\": 3518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greysia_Polii\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Greysia Polii\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greysia_Polii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greysia_Polii\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 3780, \"to\": 3812, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy  While athletes do not receive a traditional salary during their Olympic journey, they can fund their training through campaigns, sponsorships and endorsements.\", \"from\": 3813, \"to\": 3996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many Olympians earn less than $25,000 (\\u00a319,000) a year from their sport and often take on day jobs or rely on friends, family and crowdfunding to keep their athletic dreams alive.\", \"from\": 3997, \"to\": 4176, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.\", \"from\": 4178, \"to\": 4347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4315, \"end\": 4328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0223404807225003e-18, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4364, \"end\": 4377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0223404807225003e-18, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}]}"